dataIdInfo.idPurp: This dataset is intended to provide the best available statewide depiction of local fire districts in California. These include fire departments, fire protection districts, volunteer fire departments, community service districts, as well as other recognized organizations providing fire suppression services. This dataset does not include every fire district within the state such as Federal lands, reservations, or local districts which have not submitted their data to the California Department of Forestry and Fire Protection.
dataIdInfo.idAbs:
This dataset was updated March, 2024.

It has not been fully reviewed for accuracy and is intended to be used for informational purposes only.

The dataset was generated from a variety of sources including local fire districts, city governments, county governments, LAFCos, and other state agencies. Subsequent releases will include additional sources to update district boundaries, information, and fill in gaps in the dataset. As a compilation of all these sources, topological issues remain in the dataset including overlaps and the aforementioned gaps. It is the goal of CAL FIRE to fix these issues in subsequent releases which includes working with local jurisdictions.
dataIdInfo.idCredit: California Department of Forestry and Fire Protection, Contract Counties, Fire Departments, City Government, County Government, LAFCos, and other State Entities. Efforts were made to reach out to each city and fire department for their most recent data.
